Test: Two-Variable Linear Regression - Parse

Ivan Jacob Agaloos Pesigan

2021-02-11

Source: vignettes/tests/test_two-variable-regression-Parse.Rmd
test_two-variable-regression-Parse.Rmd
eq <- "
  # lhs op   rhs label   start
    e   by   y   1       NA
    y   on   x   beta    0.00
    e   with e   sigmae2 1.25
    x   with x   sigmax2 0.25
    y   on   1   alpha   0.00
    x   on   1   mux     0.50
"
ramR:::Parse(eq)
#>   lhs   op rhs   label start par.index
#> 1   e   by   y       1    NA         1
#> 2   y   on   x    beta  0.00        p1
#> 3   e with   e sigmae2  1.25        p2
#> 4   x with   x sigmax2  0.25        p3
#> 5   y   on   1   alpha  0.00        p4
#> 6   x   on   1     mux  0.50        p5
eq <- "
  # lhs op   rhs value
    e   by   y   1
    y   on   x   1
    e   with e   1
    x   with x   0.25
    y   on   1   0
    x   on   1   0.50
"
ramR:::Parse(eq)
#>   lhs   op rhs label par.index
#> 1   e   by   y  1.00      1.00
#> 2   y   on   x  1.00      1.00
#> 3   e with   e  1.00      1.00
#> 4   x with   x  0.25      0.25
#> 5   y   on   1  0.00      0.00
#> 6   x   on   1  0.50      0.50
# equality constraint
# starting values should be identical for parameters constrained to be equal
eq <- "
  # lhs op   rhs label   start
    e   by   y   1       NA
    y   on   x   beta    0.00
    e   with e   sigmax2 1.25
    x   with x   sigmax2 1.25
    y   on   1   alpha   0.00
    x   on   1   mux     0.50
"
ramR:::Parse(eq)
#>   lhs   op rhs   label start par.index
#> 1   e   by   y       1    NA         1
#> 2   y   on   x    beta  0.00        p1
#> 3   e with   e sigmax2  1.25        p2
#> 4   x with   x sigmax2  1.25        p2
#> 5   y   on   1   alpha  0.00        p3
#> 6   x   on   1     mux  0.50        p4
# `\n` and `;` as line breaks
eq <- "
    e   by   y   1       NA ; y   on   x   beta    0.00 ;
    e   with e   sigmae2 1.25 ; x   with x   sigmax2 0.25 ;
    y   on   1   alpha   0.00 \n x   on   1   mux     0.50 ;
"
ramR:::Parse(eq)
#>   lhs   op rhs   label start par.index
#> 1   e   by   y       1    NA         1
#> 2   y   on   x    beta  0.00        p1
#> 3   e with   e sigmae2  1.25        p2
#> 4   x with   x sigmax2  0.25        p3
#> 5   y   on   1   alpha  0.00        p4
#> 6   x   on   1     mux  0.50        p5
